Sentencas: This study investigates the correlation between structural/chemical properties and electrochemical performance according to the composition of the interface between the anode and the electrolyte in solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) based on mixed ion conducting material.
Titulo: Designing the Interfacial Layer between the Electrolyte and Fuel Electrode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells Operating at Intermediate Temperatures with Fuel Flexibility

Sentencas: The linear increase in the open-circuit voltage (OCV) and maximum power density (MPD) are observed as the content of the electrolyte material at the interface layer increases.
Titulo: Designing the Interfacial Layer between the Electrolyte and Fuel Electrode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells Operating at Intermediate Temperatures with Fuel Flexibility

Sentencas: The modified sample with highest performance exhibits similar to 7% higher OCV of 0.873 V and similar to 72% higher MPD of 1.38 W/cm(2) at 600 degrees C with hydrogen and similar to 8% higher OCV of 0.800 V and similar to 210% higher MPD of 0.92 W/cm(2) at 600 degrees C with methane and carbon dioxide.
Titulo: Designing the Interfacial Layer between the Electrolyte and Fuel Electrode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells Operating at Intermediate Temperatures with Fuel Flexibility

Sentencas: This result substantiates the anode structure for high performance and OCV SOFC operating with fuel flexibility.
Titulo: Designing the Interfacial Layer between the Electrolyte and Fuel Electrode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells Operating at Intermediate Temperatures with Fuel Flexibility
